The paper deals with a problem in game theory (single-elimination tournaments) and proposes new sufficient conditions for a tournament organizer to rig the tournament. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT) sub-category. The paper also involves analyzing the relationship between different tournament solutions, which could fall under the Data Structures (cs.DS) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The authors also mention probabilistic models for generating tournaments, which could fall under the Statistical Learning (cs.LG) or Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories.
